onqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Robert de Cauz was born in Shelford, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of de Cauz. He had at least 3 sons with Isabel de Ferrers. He died after 1168, in his hometown."},"et":{"–Aft 1168":"–pärast 1168","–1168":"–1168","–Female":"Surnud","1100–1168":"1100–1168","–1177":"–1177","–Male":"Surnud","1168":"1168","1100":"1100","Aft 1168":"pärast 1168","1177":"1177","Shelford, Nottinghamshire, England":"Shelford, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Shelford, , Nottingham, England":"Shelford, Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"–Aft 1168":"–1168 jälkeen","–1168":"–1168","–Female":"Kuollut","1100–1168":"1100–1168","–1177":"–1177","–Male":"Kuollut","1168":"1168","1100":"1100","Aft 1168":"1168 jälkeen","1177":"1177","Shelford, Nottinghamshire, England":"Shelford, Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Shelford, , Nottingham, England":"Shelford, Nottinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"–Aft 1168":"–après 1168","–1168":"–1168","–Female":"Décédée","1100–1168":"1100–1168","–1177":"–1177","–Male":"Décédé","1168":"1168","1100":"1100","Aft 1168":"après 1168","1177":"1177","Shelford, Nottinghamshire, England":"Shelford, Nottinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Shelford, , Nottingham, England":"Shelford, Nottinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Robert de Cauz est né à Shelford, Nottinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, fils de de Cauz. Il a eu au moins 3 fils avec Isabel de Ferrers. Il est décédé après 1168, dans sa ville natale."},"de":{"–Aft 1168":"–nach 1168","–11